Epidemiology:
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive

Control measures:
Measures applied: movement control inside the country, disinfection/disinfestation, quarantine, surveillance within containment and/or protection zone, zoning, vaccination permitted (if a vaccine exists), no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results:
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Republican Veterinary Laboratory of the West Kazakhstan (Regional Laboratory) / Cattle / polymerase chain reaction (PCR) / 2 Aug 2016 / Positive

Future reporting: the event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

Map of outbreak locations [Outbreak is in the far west of Kazakhstan, close to the border with Russia. Check it out on the OIE website. - Mod.MHJ]

--
communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[There were reports of bovine anthrax outbreaks in West Kazakhstan in 2005, 2006, 2007, and human cases in 2009, 2011, and 2014. An inheritance from the days of the USSR and its allies is to rely on human cases, not veterinary reporting. So there is a measure of inherent Kazakh underreporting certainly in the past. But they are improving, and notice that their regional diagnosis was based on a PCR test. Though from this report it is unclear whether there is enough Sterne vaccine on hand to protect the rest of the livestock in this village, the speed of their outbreak recognition and diagnostic confirmation, 3 days, is very good. - Mod.MHJ

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4402651,56.]
